  "prompt": "How much do astrophysicists make at NASA?",
  "response": "The salary of astrophysicists at NASA can vary widely depending on factors such as education level, experience, specific job role, and career grade. Generally, NASA salaries follow the federal government's General Schedule (GS) pay scale.\n\nTypical salary ranges for NASA astrophysicists:\n- Entry-level positions: $55,000 - $75,000 per year\n- Mid-career positions: $80,000 - $120,000 per year\n- Senior-level positions: $120,000 - $170,000+ per year\n\nThose with Ph.D. degrees and extensive research experience tend to earn higher salaries. Specific roles like senior research scientists or program managers can earn even more.\n\nExact salary will depend on individual qualifications, specific NASA center, and current job market conditions.",
